## ⚖️ LAN vs MAN vs WAN — Quick Comparison

| Aspect | LAN | MAN | WAN |
|---|---|---|---|
| Scope | Building/campus | City/metro | Country/continent |
| Ownership | Single org | Org or ISP/consortium | Mostly ISPs/telcos |
| Bandwidth | Highest, cheapest | High but costlier | Variable, often expensive |
| Latency | Lowest | Low-moderate | Highest (fundamental) |
| Key tech | Ethernet, switches | Fiber, DWDM, Metro Ethernet | MPLS, VPNs, BGP |
| Topology | Star, tree | Ring, hub-spoke, partial mesh | Point-to-point, hub-spoke, (partial) mesh |
| Security focus | Segmentation, ACLs, port security | Securing inter-site links | Encryption, ZTNA, IDS/IPS at egress |

