## ⚠️ Common Mistakes & Troubleshooting

### LAN
| Mistake | Fix |
|---|---|
| Oversubscription (too many devices/port, weak uplinks) | Monitor port utilization; upgrade ports/switches |
| Broadcast storms (loop or bad device) | Identify source via monitoring/systematic port disable; implement **STP** to prevent loops |
| Incorrect subnetting (too small = exhaustion, too large = huge broadcast domain) | Review addressing scheme; use subnet calculators; re-IP or add VLANs |
| Ignoring security (default creds, no segmentation, open Wi-Fi) | Regular audits; change defaults; VLANs; WPA2/WPA3 |

### MAN/WAN
| Mistake | Fix |
|---|---|
| Underestimating latency for real-time apps | Optimize apps; use WAN accelerators; re-evaluate topology |
| Insufficient bandwidth | Monitor utilization; upgrade or implement QoS |
| Single point of failure (one link/provider) | Redundant links from different providers/physical paths |
| Insecure VPNs (weak crypto, outdated protocols) | Use AES-256+, strong auth, regular config review |
| Misconfigured routing (bad BGP/internal routing) | Use routing analysis tools; review tables/BGP config carefully |

