## 🛡️ Defensive Engineering

### LAN
- **VLANs** — isolate critical systems/user groups (e.g. IoT off the main corporate network)
- **Port security** — limit/bind MAC addresses per switch port
- **ACLs** — control inter-VLAN/subnet traffic on routers/L3 switches
- **Strong auth** — passwords + MFA for admin access to network devices
- **Firmware updates** — patch known vulnerabilities regularly

### MAN/WAN
- **End-to-end encryption** — VPNs (IPsec/SSL-TLS) or app-level encryption for anything over public internet
- **ZTNA (Zero Trust Network Access)** — grant access per-resource based on identity/device posture, not just perimeter location
- **SD-WAN** — centralized management, policy enforcement, intelligent path selection, integrated firewall/encryption across branches
- **IDS/IPS** — at WAN egress and branch perimeters
- **Service provider security review** — confirm provider security meets your compliance/requirements
- **Regular audits & monitoring** — continuous anomaly detection on WAN configs/traffic

