## 📝 Chapter Summary

- **LAN** — proximity-based, high bandwidth/low latency, privately owned, Ethernet-dominant; constraints around cabling, cost, scalability, security
- **MAN** — connects LANs across a city; fiber/DWDM-based; often provider-involved; higher cost, interoperability and security challenges
- **WAN** — global reach, packet-switched, provider-dominated (MPLS, VPNs, leased lines); latency and security are the defining challenges
- Design choice always balances **cost vs performance vs control vs security** — the right answer depends on organizational scope and needs

